</ul>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">End of Event Rewards:</span></p>
<ul class="c11 lst-kix_7vapbwkl71mr-0 start">
    <li class="c3 c7 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1">Each battle has a reward of Tritons tokens being fought over. The total rewards being fought over increases depending on [alliance level, past performance?]</span>
    </li>
    <li class="c3 c7 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1">The reward is distributed to players in alliances according to the following:</span>
    </li>
</ul>
<ul class="c11 lst-kix_7vapbwkl71mr-1 start">
    <li class="c3 c16 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1">1st place: 35%</span></li>
    <li class="c3 c16 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1">2nd place: 28%</span></li>
    <li class="c3 c16 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1">3rd place: 22%</span></li>
    <li class="c3 c16 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1">4th place: 15%</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">Roughly speaking if you are in an active alliance that completes all participation checkpoints you can expect the following pantheon progression each event:</span>
</p>
<ul class="c11 lst-kix_d1416tkoyllp-0 start">
    <li class="c3 c7 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1">1 level 1 or 0.66 level 2 reward</span></li>
    <li class="c3 c7 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1">0.75 level 3 or 0.66 level 4 reward</span></li>
    <li class="c3 c7 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1">0.66 level 5 rewards</span></li>
    <li class="c3 c7 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1">Extra Tritons depending on the end of event placement.</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">Overall, the value of the participation rewards is much greater than that of the end of event placement, especially considering 4th place still gets a decent chunk of the total reward. In total, maxing out participation is worth around 3800 Tritons (using shop prices to convert) and 1st place is worth 200-1000 Tritons over last place. So if your alliance is having trouble coordinating, performing any task you can is preferable to wasting energy or hero-time waiting for instructions. </span>
</p>
<h1 class="c23" id="h.vjrrpz7hnt17"><span class="c24">Event Mechanics</span></h1>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">Atlantis provides players 4 primary actions that can be taken, each of which awards points:</span>
</p>
<ul class="c11 lst-kix_hcwkh91g36a-0 start">
    <li class="c3 c7 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1">Attack an enemy garrison slot (15 points). </span></li>
    <li class="c3 c7 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1">Repair a breached garrison slot (5 points). This requires using 5 heroes. </span>
    </li>
    <li class="c3 c7 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1">Heal your heroes or garrisoned heroes (2 points per hero).</span>
    </li>
    <li class="c3 c7 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1">Garrison a garrison slot (5 points but only if you win a battle). This requires using 5 heroes.</span>
    </li>
</ul>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">In addition to this you can withdraw garrisoned units from a garrison slot to use them elsewhere but there is an important caveat to this. See Garrisons and Defenders. </span>
</p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">You are limited to one action per site at a time, which means you cannot garrison units at a site you are repairing, nor can you repair a site at which you have units garrisoned. Other action buttons at a site are greyed out when you repair or garrison to indicate this.</span>
</p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1"><br>The remainder of the guide goes into the details of the event and potential strategies for teams to use and tactics for individual players to execute.</span>
</p>
<h2 class="c5" id="h.1cjbv0whr7jd"><span class="c10">Attacking and Atlantis Energy</span></h2>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">Alliances can only attack sites connected (via dotted lines) to one of their own. You will be attacking neutral sites (controlled by Atlantean Remnants) and sites controlled by other alliances. </span>
</p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span
        style="overflow: hidden; display: inline-block; margin: 0.00px 0.00px; border: 0.00px solid #000000; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); width: 686.16px; height: 1040.63px;"><img
        alt="" src="https://d11pry14zi9nsg.cloudfront.net/1/images/atlantis/image20.jpg"
        style="width: 686.16px; height: 1040.63px; margin-left: 0.00px; margin-top: 0.00px; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px);"
        title=""></span></p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">You can attack an enemy garrison slot for the cost of 1 Atlantis energy. Your heroes will take all the normal damage from the fight plus 20% damage from attrition. The enemy heroes will take all the normal damage from the fight plus 4% damage from attrition per hero you used. You do not need to attack with exactly 5 heroes. You will gain 15 points for initiating an attack regardless of the outcome of the fight. &nbsp;</span>
</p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">If you win the fight the enemy garrison slot will be breached and the enemy heroes will be &ldquo;knocked out&rdquo;. If you lose the fight there&rsquo;s two possible outcomes:</span>
</p>
<ol class="c11 lst-kix_u7hajjisclsd-0 start" start="1">
    <li class="c3 c7 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1">The attrition damage (4% per hero the attacker used) will KO every hero left at the end of the fight. This causes the garrison slot to be breached. </span>
    </li>
    <li class="c3 c7 li-bullet-0"><span class="c1">The attrition damage (4% per hero the attacker used) will not KO all heroes left at the end of the fight. Any KO&rsquo;d heroes are removed from the garrison to heal and any heroes left alive will remain as defenders of the slot. &nbsp;</span>
    </li>
</ol>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">Once all defending garrison slots at a site are breached, the team that breached the most slots takes control. Upon capture, the site will be given a battle shield and be immune from any attacks on garrison slots for 1 hour.</span>
</p>
<p class="c3"><span>&nbsp;</span><span
        style="overflow: hidden; display: inline-block; margin: 0.00px 0.00px; border: 0.00px solid #000000; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); width: 362.00px; height: 311.00px;"><img
        alt="" src="https://d11pry14zi9nsg.cloudfront.net/1/images/atlantis/image13.jpg"
        style="width: 362.00px; height: 311.00px; margin-left: 0.00px; margin-top: 0.00px; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px);"
        title=""></span></p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">If the enemy has no garrison in a garrison slot then a &ldquo;quick-capture&rdquo; is made available. This doesn&rsquo;t require choosing heroes but it does require at least 1 hero available. </span>
</p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span
        style="overflow: hidden; display: inline-block; margin: 0.00px 0.00px; border: 0.00px solid #000000; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); width: 661.00px; height: 416.00px;"><img
        alt="" src="https://d11pry14zi9nsg.cloudfront.net/1/images/atlantis/image6.jpg"
        style="width: 661.00px; height: 416.00px; margin-left: 0.00px; margin-top: 0.00px; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px);"
        title=""></span></p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">Atlantis Energy is generated at a rate of 1 per 2 hours, up to a maximum of 5. This means you can generate 12 x 15 = 180 participation points per day by attacking. </span>
</p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">Atlantis Energy can be bought with gems in batches of 5 up to 3 times per day at costs of 50, 100, and finally 200 gems.</span>
</p>
<h3 class="c15" id="h.tvremrtwa0wb"><span class="c6">Multiple Teams Attacking</span></h3>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">No more than 2 alliances can breach the same site, which ensures that one side will always be able to breach a majority of the garrison slots. If a 3rd team gains access to the site they cannot attack or quick-capture until one of the existing attacking team&rsquo;s breaches are repaired or one of the existing attacking teams gains control of the site. </span>
</p>
<h2 class="c5" id="h.dj2nsx1qyezs"><span class="c10">Repair</span></h2>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">You can use exactly 5 heroes at a time to repair an alliance garrison slot. This takes 2 hours by default but is reduced by 30m for each additional alliance member, up to 2, that contributes. So the minimum repair time is 1 hour. Repairing a breached garrison slot provides a &ldquo;battle shield&rdquo; which prevents that garrison slot from being attacked for 1 hr. </span>
</p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">Starting a repair awards 5 participation points. You cannot stop repairs in progress and heroes repairing do not heal passively. Sites in need of repair are easily identifiable by the smoke rising from them on the map. </span>
</p>
<p class="c3"><span
        style="overflow: hidden; display: inline-block; margin: 0.00px 0.00px; border: 0.00px solid #000000; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); width: 639.00px; height: 371.00px;"><img
        alt="" src="https://d11pry14zi9nsg.cloudfront.net/1/images/atlantis/image14.jpg"
        style="width: 639.00px; height: 371.00px; margin-left: 0.00px; margin-top: 0.00px; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px);"
        title=""></span><span class="c1">[A site in need of 2 repairs]</span></p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">Once repairs are done (or the site changes alliance control mid-repair), heroes will immediately begin healing passively again. So starting repairs then leaving the game is fine. </span>
</p>
<h2 class="c5" id="h.wzr8ntf1nwcu"><span class="c10">Healing and Knocked Out</span></h2>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">Heroes below 10% health are classified as &ldquo;Knocked out&rdquo;. They need to heal to return to &ldquo;Available&rdquo; status whence they can be used for all other tasks. </span>
</p>
<p class="c3"><span
        style="overflow: hidden; display: inline-block; margin: 0.00px 0.00px; border: 0.00px solid #000000; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); width: 307.00px; height: 310.00px;"><img
        alt="" src="https://d11pry14zi9nsg.cloudfront.net/1/images/atlantis/image12.jpg"
        style="width: 307.00px; height: 310.00px; margin-left: 0.00px; margin-top: 0.00px; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px);"
        title=""></span><span class="c1">[Knock out info blurb]</span></p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">Healing comes in two forms: passive healing and medkit healing. Passive healing occurs at a rate of 15% per hour for all heroes not garrisoned or repairing. So knocked out heroes take ~6.5 hours to fully heal. With medkits you can individually heal heroes at any alliance garrison slot, both your own heroes and your alliance mates&rsquo;. You can also heal your own heroes individually by clicking the helmet to open the hero roster then clicking on the medkit for the heroes you want to heal. Healing done via medkits awards 2 participation points per use. </span>
</p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span
        style="overflow: hidden; display: inline-block; margin: 0.00px 0.00px; border: 0.00px solid #000000; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); width: 686.50px; height: 366.00px;"><img
        alt="" src="https://d11pry14zi9nsg.cloudfront.net/1/images/atlantis/image18.jpg"
        style="width: 686.50px; height: 366.00px; margin-left: 0.00px; margin-top: 0.00px; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px);"
        title=""></span><span class="c1">[The garrison heal screen]</span></p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">Medkits are quite rare. You start with 5 and can obtain up to 25 via the alliance participation rewards. This means you can obtain up to 60 participation points per event from medkits. </span>
</p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">Medkits can be bought with gems in batches of 5 up to 3 times per day at costs of 50, 100, and finally 200 gems.</span>
</p>
<h2 class="c5" id="h.niikr03thhnf"><span class="c10">Garrisons and Defending. </span></h2>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">Garrisoning units in a garrison slot does not generate points unless you successfully defend against an attack. If you do successfully rebuff an attack, you will earn 5 participation points. You can withdraw defenders at any time but there is an important caveat. If the site being defended has any breached slots, withdrawing a garrison means leaving the slot &ldquo;Abandoned&rdquo;. Abandoned slots cannot be re-garrisoned until all breaches have been repaired. (Footnote: Presumably this is to prevent &lsquo;hot-swapping&rsquo; wounded heroes for fully healed heroes at a contested site on the front line). </span>
</p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">If attacked, your defending heroes suffer the normal damage from battle + 4% health damage per enemy hero used. </span>
</p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span
        style="overflow: hidden; display: inline-block; margin: 0.00px 0.00px; border: 0.00px solid #000000; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); width: 376.15px; height: 574.66px;"><img
        alt="" src="https://d11pry14zi9nsg.cloudfront.net/1/images/atlantis/image11.jpg"
        style="width: 376.15px; height: 574.66px; margin-left: 0.00px; margin-top: 0.00px; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px);"
        title=""></span><span class="c1">[Abandoned Garrison slot]</span></p>
<p class="c3"><span
        style="overflow: hidden; display: inline-block; margin: 0.00px 0.00px; border: 0.00px solid #000000; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); width: 687.10px; height: 480.13px;"><img
        alt="" src="https://d11pry14zi9nsg.cloudfront.net/1/images/atlantis/image19.jpg"
        style="width: 687.10px; height: 480.13px; margin-left: 0.00px; margin-top: 0.00px; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px);"
        title=""></span><span class="c1">[Garrison selection screen, 5 heroes must be used]</span></p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<h2 class="c5" id="h.3epfqqvrcp12"><span class="c10">Victory Points and Sites</span></h2>
<p class="c3"><span
        class="c1">Victory points are what determines the placement of an alliance at the end of the event. </span></p>
<p class="c0"><span class="c1"></span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c1">Each site has a certain number of garrisons and awards victory points in two ways: immediately upon breaching a garrison slot and over time upon capturing the site. The immediate reward for breaching a garrison slot is 1/10th the hourly income. </span>
</p>
